'''Wicd''' ('''W'''ireless '''i'''nterface '''c'''onnection '''d'''aemon) is a utility for managing network connections, both wired and wireless.

== Installation ==
Install {{Package|net-misc/wicd}}:
{{USEflag|package=net-misc/wicd
|X
|gtk+yes
|libnotify
|ncurses
|nls
|pm-utils+yes
}}
{{Emerge|wicd}}

[[KDE]] has its own client {{Package|kde-misc/wicd-client-kde}}:
{{Emerge|wicd-client-kde}}

== Configuration ==
After installing add wicd to the default runlevel:
{{RootCmd|rc-update add wicd}}

Be sure to remove any references to net.eth*. For net.eth0:
{{RootCmd|rc-update del net.eth0}}

Add the initscripts which were removed to the {{Path|/etc/rc.conf}} file, on the ''RC_PLUG_SERVICES'' line, by prepending exclamation points to them. For net.eth0:
{{File|/etc/rc.conf||<pre>
rc_hotplug="!net.eth0"
</pre>}}

